The paper deals with algorithms for computing centerpoints in high-dimensional spaces, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The running time analysis involves random walks, which is a technique commonly used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses applications in clustering and machine learning, which are topics in data mining (cs.DM) and control systems (cs.SY).
